                            <comment id="15306603" author="ifesdjeen" created="Mon, 30 May 2016 12:41:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that there&apos;s a race condition between the write to &lt;tt&gt;pause&lt;/tt&gt; which sets &lt;tt&gt;isActive&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; and the check for &lt;tt&gt;isEnabled&lt;/tt&gt; which reads this flag, which results into compactions activated despite the fact they shouldn&apos;t.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve ran the test with additional write lock 10 times and all 10 times it passed. Without the same lock, it was failing almost all the time on my machine. Added a multiplexed test to run &lt;tt&gt;BatchlogManagerTest&lt;/tt&gt; 50 times, too:&lt;/p&gt;

